## 16.31 Deep-seed — the eight perm tiers, one more time

For the closing, the perm vocabulary in one place:

- `read` — pure observation. Every introspection verb, every query, every projection is here. Safe by default.
- `paint` — visual side effects only. Draw a dot, place a glyph. No state mutation.
- `animate` — motion or RAF tween. Runs at full or half substrate power; skipped at quarter or paused.
- `state-change` — moves cards, focuses UI, opens/closes something. First tier that persists across the current frame.
- `destructive` — deletes data, transfers ownership. Irreversible operations.
- `financial` — money moves. Requires cart-manifest declaration.
- `network` — outbound network call. Requires cart-manifest declaration and possibly per-endpoint approval.
- `personal-data` — reads or writes user PII. Requires user consent flow.

Eight tiers. Every verb has one. Every caller has a set. Dispatch is a match: caller's set must contain the verb's requirement.

## 16.32 Deep-seed — auditing your own cart

Before you publish a cart, audit its perm usage:

```scheme
(define my-cart (read-slat-file \"my-cart.slat\"))
(define calls (extract-verb-calls my-cart))
(define perms
  (unique (map (lambda (n) (cdr (assoc 'perm (help n)))) calls)))

perms
;; => (\"read\" \"paint\" \"animate\" \"state-change\")
```

Your cart requires these four perms. Declare them in the cart's manifest. Do not declare more than you need — the sandbox will grant only what you declare, and asking for `financial` when you do not use it makes users suspicious.

## 16.33 Closing exercise

Try this on a cart file (any cart):

```scheme
(define cart (read-slat-file \"path/to/cart.slat\"))
(define verbs (extract-verb-calls cart))
(define sensitive
  (filter
    (lambda (n)
      (member (cdr (assoc 'perm (help n)))
              '(\"financial\" \"personal-data\" \"destructive\" \"network\"))))
    verbs))

sensitive
;; => any verb the cart uses with a sensitive perm
```

If sensitive is empty, the cart is low-risk. If it is not, review each entry and decide whether the cart's use of that verb is legitimate.

That is auditing at introspection speed. One filter, one review. No security scanner needed.

